phase-review: feat/hy2-live-users — Ф1 ban/unban client FRONTEND (Vue3/Vuetify/Pinia)
change: frontend submodule — Data.banClient() (POST api/ban, form-encoded, setNewData),
  Client.banned/bannedAt types, Clients.vue ban/unban action icons + confirm menu,
  ban/unban i18n keys in all 6 locales (en/fa/ru/vi/zhcn/zhtw).
review: code-reviewer + vue-reviewer ran IN PARALLEL. security review skipped per
  standing user rule (no-security-checks). Verdicts: code-reviewer APPROVE (0 CRIT/HIGH,
  1 MEDIUM); vue-reviewer BLOCK (1 HIGH + 3 MEDIUM + 1 LOW), root cause = overlay
  arrays indexed by position.
fixes applied (all CRIT/HIGH/relevant findings resolved):
  - HIGH + MEDIUM(findIndex instability): migrated BOTH delOverlay & banOverlay from
    fixed-length Array to id-keyed Record<number,boolean>; template binds [item.id];
    removes per-render findIndex.
  - MEDIUM(toggleBan no early-exit): added `if (!clients.some(id)) return` guard.
  - LOW(dynamic i18n key): switched to ternary literal keys (statically extractable).
  - MEDIUM(v-tooltip in v-menu activator): intentionally KEPT — v-menu activates on
    click, v-tooltip on mouseenter; different events, no real conflict (standalone
    unban tooltip already works). Adjudicated against vue-reviewer's claim.
verification: `docker build --target front-builder` OK (exit 0); `vue-tsc --noEmit`
  passed (id-keyed Records type-clean), vite built 807 modules in 6.16s. Backend
  contract confirmed present: api/ban -> ConfigService.BanClient (txn, audit, kick),
  model banned/bannedAt JSON, assembly filters enable=1 AND banned=0.
